The **Global Priorities Institute** (GPI) is a proposed cause prioritization research center, based in Oxford.[^main_page]

# History

The center grew out of a project run by the [Centre for Effective Altruism]().[^about_us]

The domain name for the website, `globalprioritiesinstitute.org`, was registered in July 2017.[^domain]

As of October 2017, the center is based at Oxford University but is still "undertaking the university procedures for becoming an Oxford institute".[^about_us]

In December 2017, GPI published a research agenda.[^research_agenda]

In December 2017, Michelle Hutchinson of GPI was interviewed by 80,000
Hours.[^hutchinson_interview]

